    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>A guru once thought to take a test of endurance and knowledge he called all his disciple and gave a task. All the disciple would be given an array of N distinct elements, and needs to perform at most X (1\u2264X\u2264N ) arbitrary operations. In each operation a disciple can select any element from the array and can increase it by exactly 1.</p>\n<p>A disciple can perform at max 1 operation over any element of the array.</p>\n<p>The special thing about this array is that, for any 2 elements (A[i], A[j), where (i=\u0338j), abs(A[i]\u2212A[j])\u2265K, where abs(x) denotes the absolute value of any integer x.<br /> Now, we define 3 functions:<br /> F(i,j) = Max(i,j)\u2212Min(i,j)</p>\n<p>Max(i,j) = Maximum element present in the sub array ranging from i,i+1...j in array A.</p>\n<p>Min(i,j) = Minimum element present in the sub array ranging from i,i+1..j in array A.<br /> A disciple needs to perform exactly X operations, and then needs to tell Monk the following:</p>\n<p>Answer = \u03a3Ni=1\u03a3Nj=iF(i,j)</p>\n<p>In short, a disciple needs to tell the guru the summation of the difference between the maximum and minimum element of each sub array of array A. Considering a disciple performs the X operations given to his optimally what is the maximum value of answer that they can achieve?</p>\n<p><strong>Input Format</strong>:</p>\n<p>The first line will consists of 3 space separated integers N, X and K , denoting the number of elements in the array, operations needs to be performed and minimum absolute difference between any 2 elements of the array respectively. In next line, there will be N space separated integers, A[i] , where 1\u2264i\u2264N denoting the elements of array.</p>\n<p><strong>Output Format</strong>:</p>\n<p>Print the required maximum possible value of answer.</p>\n<p><strong>Constraints</strong>:</p>\n<p>2 \u2264 N \u2264 105<br /> 1 \u2264 A[i] \u2264 106<br /> 2 \u2264 K \u2264 10<br /> Elements chosen for the operation should not violate abs(A[i]\u2212A[j]) \u2265 K.</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 2\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>Sample Input:</strong></p>\n<p>3 1 2<br /> 2 4 6<br />3<br /> <strong>Sample Output</strong>:<br />10</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>",
